					<h2>Not All Real Estate Deals Are the Same. Neither Are the Experts Who Help You Close Them.
</h2>				
		<p>Whether you’re selling your primary residence, buying a move-up home, or looking to acquire a discounted fixer-upper, there are two very different kinds of professionals you’ll want on your team:</p><p><strong>Realtors</strong><br />The go-to experts for retail transactions—serving buyers and sellers with licensed representation, market analysis, negotiations, and full-service marketing.</p><p><strong>Wholesalers</strong><br />The specialists in off-market opportunities—working with distressed sellers and investment-focused buyers to connect value-driven deals fast.</p>		
					<h2>So Who Should You Work With?
</h2>				
							<ul>
							<li>
										Want top dollar for your home? A Realtor handles marketing, negotiations, and closing with ease.
									</li>
								<li>
										Buying your next dream home? A Realtor will help you find the perfect fit and submit a competitive offer in today’s market.
									</li>
								<li>
										Looking for below-market deals? A wholesaler offers early access to off-market properties.
									</li>
						</ul>
					<h3>At Stairway Mortgage, We Work With Both—So You Get the Best of Each World.
</h3>				
		<p>Access both: licensed Realtors for retail sales and independent wholesalers for off-market buys—via our vetted network.</p>		
									<h3>
							Retail + Wholesale, Together						
					</h3>
									<p>
						We connect you with both top-performing Realtors and trusted wholesalers—so you can sell retail and shop wholesale simultaneously for max opportunity.					</p>
